# Peresvet Architecture Rules

- Keep service changes scoped to the affected domain under `src/services`.
- Shared code in `src/common` must be changed carefully because it can affect many services.
- Preserve existing service boundaries.
- Do not introduce cross-service imports that bypass established communication patterns.
- Services communicate through RabbitMQ; do not silently replace this with direct coupling.
- Avoid broad refactors unless the task explicitly requires them.
- When changing shared models, settings, RPC behavior or cache behavior, identify affected services.
- Prefer existing patterns in nearby services over new abstractions.
- Document compatibility risks in the PR summary.